HEADWORD: Helicon
<hw>Hel"i*con</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>"Elikw`n</grk>.]</ety> <def>A mountain in
B⟦oe⟧otia, in <country>Greece</country>, supposed by the Greeks to be
the residence of <persfn>Apollo</persfn> and the Muses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From <qex>Helicon's</qex> harmonious springs⟦br⟧
A thousand rills their mazy progress take.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heliconia</ent>⟦br⟧
